The paper deals with wireless communication systems and proposes a receiver design for a wireless channel model with time-varying Rayleigh fading and strong co-channel interference. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes an iterative message-passing architecture for joint channel estimation, interference mitigation, and decoding, which could fall under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the statistical properties of the interference and correlated fading in time, which could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.SI, cs.MM, and cs.LG.
